<NEW>

The unknown robot floated serenly above the comming horde of dinosaur
flesh and the very ground was begining to rumble. Trees were begining
to shake and vibrate as the steady rumbling hum of many thousands of
feet were hiting the ground.

CYCLONUS nodded at HYDRAS as he got his message.

Meanwhile the rest of HYDRAS' warriors were looking decidedly more and
more nervous as the beasts continued their relentless run in the
direction of HYDRAS' base.

At HYDRAS' message the being's optics lit up as his head, even at the
distance of nearly 30 miles or so turned to look directly at HYDRAS.

"Who is it that dares to question Saberback?" the being calls back,
"Who is it the awakens me from my thoughts?"

Around SABERBACK the dinosaurs roared, the voulme and pitch was truely
deafening, the flying reptiles swirled around him for a moment,
partially obscuring him from the Predacon's sight.
